A066668.name: Signed row sums of A066667.
formula: E.g.f. with a different offset: 1 - product {n >= 1} (1 - x^n)^(phi(n)/n) = x + x^2/2 + x^3/6 - x^4/24 - 19*x^5/120 - ..., where phi(n) = A000010(n) is the Euler totient function. Cf. A000262. - _Peter Bala_, Jan 01 2014

A066669.name: Numbers n such that phi(n) = 2^k*prime for some k >= 0.

A066670.name: Primes arising in A066669: the only odd prime divisor of phi(A066669(n)).

A066671.name: Powers of 2 arising in A066669: a(n) is the largest even divisor of EulerPhi(A066669(n)), which by definition is a power of 2.

A066672.name: Exponents of powers of 2 displayed in A066671: 2^a[n] is the largest even divisor of A066669(n).

A066673.name: Smallest term x from A066669 such that phi(x) = 2^n times some prime.

A066674.name: Least number m such that phi(m) = A000010(m) is divisible by the n-th prime.

A066675.name: a(n) = A066674(n)-1 divided by the n-th prime.

A066676.name: Smallest number m such that phi(m) is a multiple of n-th primorial number, the product of first n primes.

A066678.name: Totients of the least numbers for which the totient is divisible by n.

A066679.name: Numbers n such that sigma(n) is congruent to n mod phi(n).

A066680.name: Badly sieved numbers: as in the Sieve of Eratosthenes multiples of unmarked numbers p are marked, but only up to p^2.

A066681.name: Badly sieved numbers (A066680) which are not primes.

A066682.name: Indices of badly sieved numbers: a(n) = k if n = A066680(k), otherwise 0.

A066683.name: Number of badly sieved numbers <= n.

A066684.name: Numbers n such that prime(n) is congruent to sigma(n) (mod n), where prime(n) denotes the n-th prime.

A066685.name: Numbers n such that p(n) is congruent to EulerPhi(n) mod n, where p(n) denotes the n-th prime.

A066686.name: Array T(i,j) read by antidiagonals, where T(i,j) is the concatenation of i and j (1<=i, 1<=j).

A066687.name: Numbers n such that prime(n) == n (mod phi(n)).

A066688.name: Numbers n such that p(n) is congruent to n mod sigma(n), where p(n) denotes the n-th prime.

A066689.name: Least number k such that the square root of {k^2 + (Prime[n + k] - Prime[n])^2} is an integer; or 0 if no such number exists.

A066690.name: Odd n such that tau(n) = tau(n+2) = 10, where tau(n) = A000005(n) is the number of divisors of n.

A066691.name: Value of tau(2n-1) when tau(2n-1) = tau(2n+1).

A066692.name: Odd n such that tau(n) = tau(n+2), where tau(n) = A000005(n) is the number of divisors of n.

A066693.name: Integers whose cube root equals their number of divisors.

A066694.name: Numbers n such that phi(sigma(n)) > n.
formula: It seems that a(n) is asymptotic to C*n*log(n)^2 with C=1.38.... - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 07 2002

A066699.name: Numbers n such that binomial(2n,n)+1 is prime.

A066700.name: The leading digits in the terms in A067103 converge; dividing by a suitable power of 10 they converge to the number shown below; sequence gives continued fraction for this number.

A066701.name: Triangle giving number of nonisomorphic minimal covering designs with parameters (n, k, k-1) (designs achieving the covering number C(n,k,k-1) given in A066010), for n >= 2, 2 <= k <= n.

A066702.name: Square numbers whose reverse is triangular with the same number of digits.

A066703.name: Triangular numbers whose reverse is a square with the same number of digits.

A066705.name: Greatest k < n such that phi(k) = phi(n) if such k exists, otherwise 0.

A066706.name: Numbers n such that n divides the average of Prime(n+1) and Prime(n).

A066707.name: Incrementally largest terms in the continued fraction for Copeland-Erdos constant 0.235711... (concatenate primes).

A066708.name: Least m such that n = m mod tau(m) if such m exists, otherwise 0.

A066709.name: Triangle T(r,c) of winning binary "same game" templates.

A066710.name: RATS: Reverse Add Then Sort the digits applied to previous term, starting with 3.
formula: Let a(n) = k, form m by Reversing the digits of k, Add m to k Then Sort the digits of the sum into increasing order to get a(n+1).

A066711.name: RATS: Reverse Add Then Sort the digits applied to previous term, starting with 9.
formula: Let a(n) = k, form m by Reversing the digits of k, Add m to k Then Sort the digits of the sum into increasing order to get a(n+1).

A066712.name: Inverse of A032445, with first appearance of string "0" in decimal expansion of Pi added to A032445.

A066713.name: RATS(2^n): Reverse Add the digits of 2^n, Then Sort: a(n) = A036839(2^n).

A066714.name: Coordination sequence for ReO_3 net with respect to Re atom.
formula: a(n) = 1 if n=1 or 2*n^2+5/2-(-1)^n*(n^2+1/2) if n>1. - C. Ronaldo (aga_new_ac(AT)hotmail.com), Dec 13 2004

A066716.name: Decimal expansion of the binary Champernowne constant 0.862240125868... whose binary expansion is the concatenation of 1, 2, 3, ... written in binary.
formula: The "binary" Champernowne constant is the number whose base-2 expansion is the concatenation of the binary representations of the integers, 0.(1)(10)(11)(100)(101)(110)(111)(1000)..., cf. A030302.

A066717.name: The continued fraction for the "binary" Champernowne constant.

A066718.name: Incrementally largest terms in the continued fraction for the "binary" Champernowne constant.

A066719.name: Numbers n such that 1+n^phi(n) is prime.

A066720.name: The greedy rational packing sequence: a(1) = 1; for n > 1, a(n) is smallest number such that the ratios a(i)/a(j) for 1 <= i < j <= n are all distinct.

A066722.name: Numbers that can be expressed as the sum of two primes in exactly six ways.

A066723.name: Number of distinct partitions of n-th triangular number which can be obtained by merging parts in the partition 1+2+...+n.

A066724.name: a(1) = 1, a(2) = 2; for n > 1, a(n) is the least integer > a(n-1) such that the products a(i)*a(j) for 1 <= i < j <= n are all distinct.

A066725.name: Primes p the product of whose digits increased by one is prime.
formula: A084354 MINUS A011540. - _R. J. Mathar_, Aug 26 2007

A066726.name: Numbers n such that binomial(2n, n) - 1 is prime.

A066728.name: a(n) is the number of integers of the form (n+k+n*k)/(n-k) for k = 1,2,...,n-1.
formula: a(n) = ceiling( d(n*(n+2)) / 2 ) - 1, where d(n) = number of divisors of n (A000005). - Antonio G. Astudillo (afg_astudillo(AT)lycos.com), Jul 02 2003

A066729.name: a(n) = Product_{d|n, d<n} d if n is composite, n otherwise.
formula: a(n) = n^c(n) * ( Product_{d|n, d<n} d )^(1-c(n)), where c is the prime characteristic (A010051). - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jan 10 2021

A066731.name: f-triperfect numbers, where f(n) = sigma(n) and f-triperfect numbers are defined similarly to f-perfect numbers in A066218.

A066732.name: Least k such that the least factor of k^Phi(k) -1 is the n-th prime.

A066733.name: Numbers such that the nonzero product of the digits of its square is also a square.

A066734.name: Numbers such that the nonzero product of the digits of its 4th power is also a 4th power.

A066735.name: Primes p dividing 1 + the product of the primes less than p.

A066736.name: Least number > 1 such that the nonzero product of the digits of its n-th power is also an n-th power.

A066737.name: Composite numbers that are concatenations of primes.

A066738.name: Primes that are concatenations of nonprime numbers.

A066739.name: Number of representations of n as a sum of products of positive integers. 1 is not allowed as a factor, unless it is the only factor. Representations which differ only in the order of terms or factors are considered equivalent.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{pi} Product_{m=1..n} binomial(k(m)+A001055(m)-1, k(m)), where pi runs through all partitions k(1) + 2 * k( 2) + ... + n * k(n) = n. a(n)=1/n*Sum_{m=1..n} a(n-m)*b(m), n > 0, a(0)=1, b(m)=Sum_{d|m} d*A001055(d). Euler transform of A001055(n): Product_{m=1..infinity} (1-x^m)^(-A001055(m)). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Jan 21 2002

A066740.name: Number of distinct partitions of A007504(n) which can be obtained by merging parts in the partition 2+3+5+...+prime(n), where prime(n) is the n-th prime.

A066741.name: Pentagonal numbers not divisible by 10 whose reverse is a square.

A066742.name: Square numbers not divisible by 10 whose reverse is pentagonal.

A066743.name: a(n) is the number of integers of the form (n^2+1)/(k^2+1), where k = 1,2,3,...,n.
formula: Conjecture: (1/n)*Sum_{i=1..n} a(i) = c*log(log(n)) asymptotically with 1 < c < 2.

A066744.name: a(n) = either 4a(n-1)+1 or 4a(n-1)+3 depending on corresponding term of A005614, +3 for 0, +1 for 1.

A066745.name: Least number of applications of f(k) = k(k+1)+1 to n to yield a prime, if this number exists; 0 otherwise.

A066746.name: Conjectured values of a(n) defined by a(n) = least number of applications of f(k) = k^2 + 1 to n to yield a prime, if this number exists; = -1 otherwise.

A066747.name: Decimal expansion of the "binary" Copeland-Erdős constant 0.734121515408286120606...: concatenate primes in base two.

A066748.name: The continued fraction for the "binary" Copeland-Erdos constant.

A066749.name: List of primes p which are equal to a central binomial coefficient C(n,floor(n/2)) plus 1.

A066750.name: Greatest common divisor of n and its digit sum.

A066751.name: Triangular numbers whose reverse is prime.

A066753.name: a(n) = least natural number k such that n + Sum_{i=1..k} prime(i) is prime if such k exists; = 0 otherwise.

A066754.name: Incrementally largest terms in the continued fraction for the "binary" Copeland-Erdos constant.

A066755.name: Numbers n such that n^2 + 1 is not divisible by k^2 + 1 for any k in [1,n-1].

A066756.name: Smallest number that requires n^3 steps to reach 1 in its Collatz trajectory (counting x/2 and 3x+1 steps).
formula: Mapping at each step for Collatz problem: x -> x/2 if n is even, else x -> 3*x+1; count the steps until x=1.

A066757.name: Pentagonal numbers not divisible by 10 whose reverse is triangular.

A066758.name: Triangular numbers not divisible by 10 whose reverse is pentagonal.

A066759.name: a(n) = least multiple of n differing from a prime by at most 1, if such a multiple exists; = 0 otherwise.

A066760.name: Sum_{1<=k<=n, k is not a divisor of n and k is not coprime to n} k.
formula: a(n) = 0 if and only if n = 1, 4 or a prime. - _Robert G. Wilson v_, Jul 31 2004

A066761.name: Number of positive integers of the form (n^2+k^2)/(n-k) for k=1,2,3,4,....,n-1.
formula: No general formula is known but let k be a positive integer, p and q distinct odd primes then a(2^k)=k a(p^k)=2*k a(p*q)= 7 or 8 if p >13 a(2*p)= 5 if p>5 a(9*p^2)= 23 .... Asymptotic formula: (1/n)*sum(i=1, n, a(i))= log(n)*log(log(n))+o(log(n)).

A066763.name: Numbers n such that (n, phi(n)) lies on a circle with integral radius centered at the origin, i.e., n^2 + phi(n)^2 is a square.

A066764.name: Numbers n such that (n, sigma(n)) lies on a circle with integral radius centered at the origin, i.e., n^2 + sigma(n)^2 is a square.

A066765.name: Numbers n such that phi(n) < n/5.

A066766.name: Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} sigma(k)/2^k where sigma(k) is the sum of divisors of k, 1 <= d <= k.
formula: Faster converging series: Sum_{n >= 1} (1/2)^(n^2) * (n*(4^n - 1) + 2^n)/(2^n - 1)^2. - _Peter Bala_, Jan 19 2021

A066768.name: Sum_{d|n} binomial(2*d-2,d-1).
formula: G.f.: Sum_{n>=1} x^n/sqrt(1-4*x^n). [From Paul D. Hanna, Aug 23 2011]
Logarithmic derivative of A052854, the number of unordered forests on n nodes.
Equals A051731 * A000984, i.e. the inverse Mobius transform of A000984. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Nov 09 2007

A066770.name: a(n) = 5^n*sin(2n*arctan(1/2)) or numerator of tan(2n*arctan(1/2)).
formula: a(n) = 5^n*sin(2*n*arctan(1/2)). A recursive formula for T(n) = tan(2*n*arctan(1/2)) is T(n+1) = (4/3+T(n))/(1-4/3*T(n)). Unsigned a(n) is the absolute value of numerator of T(n).
a(n) is the imaginary part of (2+I)^(2*n) = Sum_{k=0..n} 2^(2*n-2*k-1)*(-1)^k*binomial(2*n, 2*k+1). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 03 2002
a(n) = 5^n*sin(n*x), where x = arcsin(4/5) = 0.927295218.. . - _Gary Detlefs_, Dec 11 2010

A066771.name: 5^n cos(2n arctan(1/2)) or denominator of tan(2n arctan(1/2)).
formula: A recursive formula for T(n) = tan(2n arctan(1/2)) is T(n+1)=(4/3+T(n))/(1-4/3*T(n)). Unsigned A(n) is the absolute value of the denominator of T(n).
a(n) is the real part of (2+I)^(2n) = sum(k=0, n, 4^(n-k)*(-1)^k*C(2n, 2k) ). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 03 2002
a(n) = real part of (3 + 4i)^n. - _Gary W. Adamson_, Aug 06 2006

A066772.name: Continued fraction expansion for Sum_{k=1..inf} d(k)/2^k where d(k) are divisors of k, 1<=d<=k.

A066773.name: Smallest number which requires n^2 steps in the 3x+1 problem.

A066774.name: A066728(a(n))=3.
formula: If a(k+1)-a(k)=2 then a(k) or a(k+1) is prime. For example : a(9)-a(8)=37-35 and a(9)=37 is prime. a(16)-a(15)=69-67=2 and a(15)=67 is prime.

A066775.name: Primes p such that 2*p^2 is not in A066721.

A066776.name: Numbers n such that A043347(n) is a prime.

A066777.name: First differences of Stern's sequence A005230.

A066779.name: Sum of squarefree numbers <= n.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{d=1..sqrt(n)} mu(d)*d^2*floor(n/d^2)*floor(n/d^2+1)/2. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Apr 26 2012
G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} mu(k)^2*k*x^k/(1 - x). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 16 2017

A066780.name: a(n) = Product_{k=1..n} sigma(k); sigma(k) is the sum of the positive divisors of n.

A066782.name: Numbers n such that (n, phi(n)) lies on the hyperbola x^2 - y^2 = m^2, for some natural number m, i.e., n^2 - phi(n)^2 = m^2.

A066783.name: Integers of the form (prime(k)+1)/phi(k), by order of appearance.

A066784.name: Numbers n such that (n, sigma(n)) lies on the hyperbola y^2 - x^2 = m^2, for some natural number m, i.e., sigma(n)^2 - n^2 = m^2.

A066785.name: Numbers n such that (n, phi(n), sigma(n)) lies on a sphere with integral radius centered at the origin, i.e., n^2 + phi(n)^2 + sigma(n)^2 is a square.

A066786.name: a(n) is the least k such that the distance between (n, phi(n)) and (n+k, phi(n+k)) is an integer (i.e., k^2 + (phi(n+k) - phi(n))^2 is a square), or 0 if none exists.

A066790.name: a(n) = least natural number k such that the distance between (n, sigma(n)) and (n+k, sigma(n+k)) is an integer (i.e., k^2 + (sigma(n+k) - sigma(n))^2 is a square), if such k exists; 0 otherwise.

A066793.name: The start of a record-breaking run of consecutive integers with an even number of prime factors.

A066794.name: Start of a record-breaking run of consecutive integers with an odd number of prime factors.

A066796.name: a(n) = Sum_{i=1..n} binomial(2*i,i).
formula: a(n) = A006134(n) - 1; generating function: (sqrt(1-4*x)-1)/(sqrt(1-4*x)*(x-1)) - Antonio G. Astudillo (afg_astudillo(AT)hotmail.com), Feb 11 2003, corrected by _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 06 2012

A066799.name: Square array read by antidiagonals of eventual period of powers of k mod n; period of repeating digits of 1/n in base k.
formula: T(n, k) = T(n, k-n) if k > n.

A066800.name: Number of different eventual period lengths for power sequences mod n; i.e., number of different period lengths of repeating digits of 1/n in different bases.
formula: Number of divisors of reduced totient function: a(n) = A000005(A002322(n)).

A066801.name: A self-generating sequence: let S = {}, a(0) = 333; for n >= 1, factorize a(n-1), arrange prime factors in increasing order and append their digits to S; then a(n) is the 3-digit number formed from terms 3n, 3n+1, 3n+2 of S. Leading zeros are omitted from a(n).

A066802.name: a(n) = binomial(6*n,3*n).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{i=0..n} Sum_{j=0..n} Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(n, i)*binomial(n, j) *binomial(n, k)*binomial(3n, i+j+k). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Mar 08 2005

O.g.f.(with a(0):=1): (cb(x^(1/3)) + sqrt(2)*P(x^(1/3))*sqrt(1/P(x^(1/3))+1+2*x^(1/3)))/3, with cb(x):=1/sqrt(1-4*x) (o.g.f. of A000984) and P(x):=P(-1/2,4*x)= 1/sqrt(1+4*x+16*x^2) (o.g.f. of A116091, with P(x,z) the o.g.f. of the Legendre polynomials). - _Wolfdieter Lang_, Mar 24 2011
Supercongruences: a(m*p^k) == a(m*p^(k-1)) ( mod p^(3*k) ) for prime p >= 5 and positive integers m and k.

A066804.name: Sum of diagonal elements and those below it for a square matrix of integers, starting with 1.

A066805.name: a(n) is the least k such that n + Sum_{i=1..k} A018252(i) is prime; or 0 if none exists.

A066808.name: F(n)-1 mod 2^n+1 with F(n)= n-th Fermat number = 1+2^2^n.
formula: F(n)-1=1 mod (2^n+1) for all n=2^k because F(n)=2+ F(1)F(2)..F(n-1)

A066809.name: a(n) = sum of modular offsets: mod[n+c,b]-(mod[n,b]+c) for c<=b<=n.

A066810.name: Expansion of x^2/((1-3*x)*(1-2*x)^2).
formula: Inverse binomial transform of A086443. - _Ross La Haye_, Apr 29 2006
Convolution of A000244 beginning [0,1,3,9,27,81,...] and A001787. - _Ross La Haye_, Feb 15 2007

A066811.name: Numbers k such that the concatenation of odd numbers from 1 to k is a prime.

A066812.name: a(n) is such that phi(a(n)+1) = phi(a(n)-1).
formula: Conjecture: there is a constant 2 < c < 2.1 such that a(n)=n^c asymptotically.

A066814.name: Smallest prime p such that (p-1) has n divisors, or 0 if no such prime exists.

A066815.name: Number of partitions of n into sums of products.

A066817.name: Conjectured values of first prime in the orbit f(m), f(f(m)), ..., where f(n) = A067599(n) and m = n-th composite number; or 0 if none exists.

A066818.name: a(n) is the least k such that n + Sum_{i=1..k} A005384(i) is prime; or 0 if none exists.

A066819.name: Sum of the first n Sophie Germain primes.

A066821.name: Numbers n such that phi(n^2-1)/(n-1) is an integer.

A066822.name: The fourth column of A038622, triangular array that counts rooted polyominoes.

A066823.name: Primes in the main diagonal of the Stolarsky array (cf. A035506).

A066824.name: Sum of the reciprocals of the partitions of n enumerated in A058360.

A066825.name: a(1) = 1; set of digits of a(n)^2 is a subset of the set of digits of a(n+1)^2.

A066826.name: Numbers n such that n divides the average of Prime(n-1) and Prime(n).

A066827.name: a(n) = gcd(2^((n*(n+1)/2)) + 1, 2^n + 1).
formula: If n is not congruent to 1 mod 4, a(n) = 1. If n is congruent to 1 mod 4, a(n) = 2^n + 1.

A066828.name: Numbers n such that n divides the average of Prime(n-1) and Prime(n+1).

A066829.name: 1 if product of odd number of primes; 0 if product of even number of primes.
formula: a(m*n) = a(m) XOR a(n). [_Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 28 2008]

A066831.name: Numbers n such that sigma(n) divides sigma(phi(n)).

A066833.name: Continued fraction expansion of Product_{p prime} (1-1/(p^4-p^3)).

A066834.name: Continued fraction expansion of Product_{p prime} (1-1/(p^5-p^4)).

A066835.name: a(n) = omega((prime(n)-1)! + 1), where omega is given by A001221, primes in A000040.

A066836.name: Least number k such that k divides the average of prime(k-n) and prime(k+n).

A066837.name: Least number k such that for the average of n consecutive primes, beginning with the k-th prime, is divisible by the average of their indices.

A066838.name: Product of primes < n that do not divide n.
formula: a(n) = e^[Sum_{k=2..n} (1-floor(n/k)+floor((n-1)/k))*A010051(k)*M(k)] where M(n) is the Mangoldt function. - _Anthony Browne_, Jun 17 2016

A066839.name: a(n) = sum of positive divisors k of n with k <= sqrt(n).
formula: a(n) = Sum_{i=1..floor(sqrt(n))} (-(n mod i) + (n-1) mod i + 1). - _José de Jesús Camacho Medina_, Feb 21 2021

A066840.name: Sum of positive integers k where k <= n/2 and gcd(k,n) = 1.
formula: For odd prime p, a(p) = (p^2-1)/8. - _Thomas Ordowski_, Nov 12 2014
Conjecture: a(n) = n*phi(n)/8 + O(n). - _Thomas Ordowski_, Nov 12 2014
G.f.: Sum_{n>=1} mu(n)*n*x^(2*n)/((1-x^n)*(1-x^(2*n))^2), where mu(n)=A008683(n). - _Mamuka Jibladze_, Apr 05 2015
For odd prime p and e>0, a(p^e) = (p^(2e-1)+1)*(p-1)/8; a(2^e) = 4^(e-2) for e>1 (and a(2)=1). - _Mamuka Jibladze_, Apr 10 2015
If n == 0 (mod 4) then a(n) = n*phi(n)/8. - _Robert Israel_, Apr 13 2015
If n is prime then a(n) = binomial(1 + floor(n/2), 2). - _David A. Corneth_, Apr 14 2015
a(n) = (1/2) * Sum_{k=1..n} k * [gcd(k,2*n-k) = 2], where [ ] is the Iverson bracket. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Jun 07 2021

A066841.name: a(n) = Product{k|n} k^(n/k); product is over the positive divisors of n.

A066842.name: a(n) = Product_{k|n} k^k; product is over the positive divisors, k, of n.

A066843.name: a(n) = Product_{k=1..n} d(k); d(k) is the number of positive divisors of k.

A066846.name: Numbers of the form a^a + b^b, a >= b > 0.

A066847.name: Integers of the form m! + n!, m and n = positive integers.

A066848.name: Consider sequence of fractions A066657/A066658 produced by ratios of terms in A066720; let m = smallest integer such that all fractions 1/n, 2/n, ..., (n-1)/n have appeared when we reach A066720(m) = k; sequence gives values of k; set a(n) = -1 if some fraction i/n never appears.

A066849.name: Consider sequence of fractions A066657/A066658 produced by ratios of terms in A066720; let m = smallest integer such that all fractions 1/n, 2/n, ..., (n-1)/n have appeared when we reach A066720(m) = k; sequence gives values of m; set a(n) = -1 if some fraction i/n never appears.

A066850.name: Numbers n such that phi(phi(n)) + sigma(sigma(n)) = phi(sigma(n)) + sigma(phi(n)), where phi=A000010 is Euler's totient function and sigma=A000203 is the sum of divisors function.

A066851.name: Number of ordered solutions (x,y,z) to xy + yz + zx = n with x,y,z >= 1.

A066853.name: Number of different remainders (or residues) for the Fibonacci numbers (A000045) when divided by n (i.e., the size of the set of F(i) mod n over all i).

A066854.name: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..8} 2^(8-k) * c(16n+2k+1), where c(j) is 1 if j is composite, 0 if j is prime.

A066855.name: Triangle T(n,k) of numbers of representations of n as a sum of k products of positive integers, k=1..n. 1 is not allowed as a factor, unless it is the only factor.Representations which differ only in the order of terms or factors are considered equivalent.
formula: G.f.: Product_{m=1..infinity} (1-y*x^m)^(-A001055(m)). T(n, k) = Sum_{pi} Product_{m=1..n} binomial(p(m)+A001055(m)-1, p(m)), where pi runs through all nonnegative solutions of p(1)+2*p(2)+...+n*p(n)=n, p(1)+p(2)+...+p(n)=k.

A066856.name: a(n) = omega(n!+1), where omega is the number of distinct primes dividing n, A001221.

A066857.name: Smallest number k such that n! - k is a square

A066858.name: Smallest k>1 such that for each integer x, x^k=x or x^k=0 (mod n); or 0 if no such k exists.

A066859.name: Product of sums of divisors and non-divisors.

A066860.name: The sum of the non-divisors of n (less than n) is a multiple of the sum of the divisors of n.

A066861.name: For x > 0 let f(x) = x/2 if x is even, f(x) = (3*x+1)/2 if x is odd (3x+1 or Collatz problem). Sequence gives numbers such that k-1 applications of f lead to k for some k > 0.

A066862.name: Numbers k such that k divides Sum_{i=1..k} gcd(k,i) = A018804(k).
formula: If n = 4^k with k >= 0, n is in the sequence.
If p is prime and k >= 0 then n = p^(kp) is in the sequence. - _Thomas Ordowski_, Oct 28 2014

A066863.name: Number of binary arrangements without adjacent 1's on n X n staggered hexagonal grid.

A066864.name: Number of binary arrangements without adjacent 1's on n X n rhombic hexagonal grid.

A066865.name: Number of binary arrangements without adjacent 1's on n X n staggered hexagonal torus bent for odd n.

A066866.name: Number of binary arrangements without adjacent 1's in n X n rhombic hexagonal grid torus.

A066867.name: Numbers n such that 2^n has 7 as its fourth decimal digit from the right.

A066868.name: a(n) is the least k such that n + Sum_{i=1..k} A005385(i) is prime; or 0 if none exists.

A066869.name: Sum of the first n safe primes.

A066870.name: Happy amicable pairs: numbers which belong to an amicable pair in which both terms are happy numbers.

A066871.name: Harshad (or Niven) amicable pairs: numbers which belong to an amicable pair in which both terms are Harshad (or Niven) numbers.

A066872.name: p^2 + 1 as p runs through the primes.

A066873.name: Number of amicable pairs where smaller term of the pair is less than 10^n.

A066874.name: Number of partitions of n into unitary divisors of n.

A066875.name: Numbers n such that prime(n+1) + prime(n-1) = 2*prime(n).

A066876.name: Numbers n such that prime(n+2) + prime(n-2) = 2*prime(n).

A066877.name: a(n) = omega(n!-1), where omega is the number of distinct primes dividing n, A001221.

A066878.name: Primes of the form p^3 - 2 where p is prime.

A066879.name: n such that there are as many 1's as 0's in the base 2 expansion of Floor(n/2).

A066880.name: Biased numbers: n such that all terms of the sequence f(n), f(f(n)), f(f(f(n))), ..., 1, where f(k) = Floor(k/2), are odd.

A066881.name: Numbers n such that sigma(phi(n))/sigma(n) is an integer >= 4.

A066882.name: Number of partitions of n into prime divisors of n.
formula: Coefficient of x^n in expansion of 1/Product_{d is prime divisor of n} (1-x^d). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Apr 11 2004

A066883.name: Number of primes in the interval [p(n), p(n)^2] minus p(n), where p(n) is the n-th prime.

A066884.name: Square array read by antidiagonals where the n-th row contains the positive integers with n binary 1's.

A066886.name: Sum of the elements in any transversal of a prime(n) X prime(n) array containing the numbers from 1 to prime(n)^2 in standard order.
formula: a(n) = prime(n)*(prime(n)^2+1)/2, where prime(n) is the n-th prime.
a(n) = A006254(n-1)^4 - A005097(n-1)^4, for n>1. - _Dimitris Valianatos_, Apr 10 2018

A066887.name: Numbers n such that OMEGA(phi(n)) = OMEGA(n) where phi is the Euler totient function and OMEGA(x) is the number of repeated prime factors in x.

A066888.name: Number of primes p between triangular numbers T(n) < p <= T(n+1).
formula: a(n) equals the number of occurrences of n+1 in A057062. - _Esko Ranta_, Jul 29 2011

A066889.name: a(n) = g(P(n)+2) - P(n), where P(n) = Product_{k=1..n} Fibonacci(k) and g(i) is the smallest prime >= i.

A066890.name: Cubes that are the sum of three distinct positive cubes.

A066893.name: Numbers k such that k divides (prime(3*k) - prime(2*k)).

A066895.name: Numbers k such that k divides prime(k) + prime(k+1).

A066897.name: Total number of odd parts in all partitions of n.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} b(k)*numbpart(n-k), where b(k)=A001227(k)=number of odd divisors of k and numbpart() is A000041. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Jan 26 2002
a(n) ~ exp(Pi*sqrt(2*n/3)) * (2*gamma + log(24*n/Pi^2)) / (8*Pi*sqrt(2*n)), where gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant A001620. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 25 2018

A066898.name: Total number of even parts in all partitions of n.
formula: G.f.: sum(x^(2j)/(1-x^(2j)), j=1..infinity)/product((1-x^j), j=1..infinity). - _Emeric Deutsch_, Feb 17 2006
a(n) ~ exp(Pi*sqrt(2*n/3)) * (2*gamma + log(3*n/(2*Pi^2))) / (8*Pi*sqrt(2*n)), where gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant A001620. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, May 25 2018

A066901.name: Let phi(k) determine the x-coordinate and prime(k) the y-coordinate of the point A(k). Sequence gives values of n such that points A(n), A(n+1) and A(n+2) form a right triangle with right angle at A(n+1).

A066902.name: Integers k such that phi(prime(k)+1) = phi(prime(k)-1).

A066906.name: Places n where A006577(n) is a prime number.

A066907.name: Number of elements in GL(2,Z_n) x with x^2 == I mod n where I is the identity matrix.

A066908.name: n^n minus largest factorial less than or equal to n^n.

A066909.name: (product of primes < n that do not divide n) (mod n).
formula: a(n) = A066838(n) modulo n. - _Michel Marcus_, May 20 2014

A066910.name: a(1) = 1; a(n+1) = (sum{k=1 to n} a(k) ) (mod n).

A066911.name: Sum of primes < n that do not divide n.

A066912.name: Fourth column of the Eulerian triangle A008292 in square array format.

A066913.name: (sum of primes < n that do not divide n) (mod n).
formula: a(n) = A066911(n) modulo n. - _Michel Marcus_, May 20 2014

A066917.name: Determinant of n X n matrix whose rows are cyclic permutations of 4..Composite(n).

A066918.name: a(n) = least natural number k such that f(k) begins a maximal zigzag of length n in the prime gaps function f(x) = p(x+1)-p(x), where p(x) denotes the x-th prime. (Cf. A066485.)

A066919.name: a(n) = least number of applications of f to n to reach 1, where f is defined by f(n) = phi(n) if n is even; = sigma(n) if n is odd.

A066920.name: Number of partitions of n into lucky parts.

A066923.name: Let f(x) = phi(x) + sigma(x); a(n) = least k such that at k begins a maximal run of length n of consecutive strict local extrema of f, or 0 if no such k exists.

A066924.name: Numbers n such that the GCD of n and the Chowla's function of n (A048050) is >= n/3.

A066925.name: Numbers n having a partition n=sum x_i for which sum n/x_i is the same partition of n.

A066926.name: Numbers n having a partition n=sum x_i for which sum n/x_i is also a partition of n.

A066927.name: Least k such that between p and 2p, for all primes > 3, there is always a number that is twice a square, i.e.; a k such that p < 2k^2 < 2p.

A066928.name: Numbers n such that floor(n*log(n)) is prime.

A066929.name: Numbers n such that Omega(n) = floor(log(n)).

A066930.name: Numbers n such that phi(sigma(n)) divides sigma(phi(n)).

A066931.name: Number of ways to tile hexagon of edge n with diamonds of side 1, not counting rotations and reflections as different.

A066932.name: a(n) is the denominator of b(n) where b(n)=1/b(n-1)+1/b(n-2) with b(1)=1 and b(2)=2.
formula: a(n) is the numerator of b(n) where b(n)=1/(b(n-1)+ b(n-2)) with b(1)=1 and b(2)=2 [From _Mark Dols_, Jul 17 2009]

A066933.name: Determinant of n X n matrix whose rows are cyclic permutations of 2..prime(n).
formula: Conjecture: a(n) = (-1)^(n+floor(n/2))*Res(f(n) , x^n - 1), where Res is the resultant, and f(n)=Sum_{k=1..n} prime(k)*x^k. - _Benedict W. J. Irwin_, Dec 07 2016

A066934.name: Composite solutions of phi(n)==1 (mod bigomega(n)) where phi(n)=A000010(n) is the Euler totient function and bigomega(n)=A001222(n) is the number of prime divisors of n (counted with multiplicity).

A066935.name: bigomega(n+1)==0 (mod bigomega(n)) where bigomega(n)=A001222(n) is the number of prime divisors of n (counted with multiplicity).

A066936.name: Integers k such that prime(k)-1 == 0 (mod phi(k)) where prime(n)=A000040(n) is the n-th prime and phi(n)=A000010(n) is the Euler totient function.

A066937.name: For n=1,2,3,..., define b(n) as follows: initialize v at v=n; then for k=2,3,4,..., if v>0 and k divides v, replace v with v-k. Set b(n)=v. Then {a(n)} is the subsequence consisting of the nonzero terms of {b(n)}.

A066938.name: Primes of the form p*q+p+q, where p and q are primes.

A066939.name: Numbers n such that phi(phi(n)) + sigma(sigma(n)) - phi(sigma(n)) - sigma(phi(n)) = phi(n) + sigma(n).

A066940.name: Numbers n such that gcd(prime(n+1) + 1, prime(n) + 1) = 2.

A066941.name: Numbers n such that gcd(prime(n+1) + 1, prime(n) + 1) = 4.

A066942.name: Numbers n such that gcd(prime(n+1) + 1, prime(n) + 1) = 6.

A066943.name: Numbers n such that gcd(prime(n+1) + 1, prime(n) + 1) = 8.

A066944.name: Numbers n such that gcd(prime(n+1) + 1, prime(n) + 1) = 10.

A066945.name: Numbers n such that phi(phi(n)) + sigma(sigma(n)) - phi(sigma(n)) - sigma(phi(n)) = phi(n).

A066946.name: Numbers n such that phi(phi(n)) + sigma(sigma(n)) - phi(sigma(n)) - sigma(phi(n)) = sigma(n).

A066947.name: Number of elements of order 2 in GL(2,Z_n).
formula: If n = 2^m*p^a...q^b where p, ..., q are the odd prime divisors of n, then a(n) = c(m)*(p^{2a} + p^{2a-1} + 2)...(q^{2b} + q^{2b-1} + 2) - 1 where c(0) = 1, c(1) = 4, c(2) = 28 and c(m) = 9*4^{m-1} + 32 for m > 2. The integer function f(n) = a(n)+1 is multiplicative, i.e., f(m*n)=f(m)*f(n) for coprime m and n. - Alec Mihailovs (alec(AT)mihailovs.com), Mar 24 2002
a(n) = A227867(n) - 1 for odd n. - _Jianing Song_, Jul 08 2018

A066948.name: Triangle of prime signature of A007870(n), read by rows.

A066949.name: Take the sum of the previous two terms, subtract n if this sum is greater than n.

A066950.name: Numbers n such that phi(sigma(n)) + sigma(phi(n)) = 2n.

A066951.name: Number of nonisomorphic connected graphs that can be drawn in the plane using n unit-length edges.

A066952.name: Smallest m such that A072410(m) = n.

A066955.name: Number of unordered solutions of xy+yz+zx=n, x,y,z>0.

A066956.name: a(n) = number of ways of placing '+' and '-' among the digits 123456789 so that the result of the expression is n, '-' before 1 not allowed.

A066957.name: a(n) = number of ways of placing '+' and '-' among the digits 123456789 so that the result of the expression is n, '-' before 1 IS allowed.

A066958.name: Number of ordered primitive solutions (x,y,z) to xy + yz + zx = n with x,y,z >= 1.

A066959.name: Bigomega(n^n) where bigomega(x) is the number of prime factors in x (counted with multiplicity).
formula: Defined by a(p) = p for p prime and a(mn) = a(m)*n + m*a(n). An analogous sequence with a(p) = 1 is A003415. - _David W. Wilson_, Mar 02 2011
G.f.: x*f'(x), where f(x) = Sum_{p prime, k>=1} x^(p^k)/(1 - x^(p^k)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 10 2017

A066961.name: Numbers n such that sigma(n) divides sigma(sigma(n)).

A066963.name: Start of a record-breaking run of consecutive composite integers with an odd number of prime factors.

A066966.name: Total sum of even parts in all partitions of n.

A066967.name: Total sum of odd parts in all partitions of n.
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} b(k)*numbpart(n-k), where b(k)=A000593(k)=sum of odd divisors of k.
G.f.: sum((2i-1)x^(2i-1)/(1-x^(2i-1)), i=1..infinity)/product(1-x^j, j=1..infinity). - _Emeric Deutsch_, Feb 19 2006

A066969.name: Numbers k such that Sum_{i=1..k} phi(i)/gcd(k,i) is an integer.
formula: If k = 4^j, j >= 0, k is in the sequence.

A066980.name: Numbers k such that antid(k) > antid(k+1) and santid(k) > santid(k+1), where antid(k) = A066272 and santid(k) = A066417.

A066981.name: Number of residues of Lucas numbers modulo n.

A066985.name: Reflective numbers: n such that the decimal encoding of the prime factorization of n (A067599) is palindronomic.

A066986.name: Integers of the form (Product_{i=1..k} sigma(i))/(Product_{i=1..k} phi(i)) = A066780(k)/A001088(k).

A066989.name: a(n) = (n!)^3 * Sum_{i=1..n} 1/i^3.
formula: Recurrence: a(1) = 1, a(2) = 9, a(n+2) = (2*n+3)*(n^2+3*n+3)*a(n+1) - (n+1)^6*a(n). b(n) = n!^3 satisfies the same recurrence with the initial conditions b(1) = 1, b(2) = 8. Hence we obtain the finite continued fraction expansion a(n)/b(n) = 1/(1-1^6/(9-2^6/(35-3^6/(91-...-(n-1)^6/((2n-1)*(n^2-n+1)))))) for n >= 2, leading to the infinite continued fraction expansion zeta(3) = 1/(1-1^6/(9-2^6/(35-3^6/(91-...-(n-1)^6/((2n-1)*(n^2-n+1)-...))))). Compare with A001819. - _Peter Bala_, Jul 19 2008
a(n) ~ Zeta(3) * (2*Pi)^(3/2) * n^(3*n+3/2) / exp(3*n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 27 2017
Sum_{n>=1} a(n) * x^n / (n!)^3 = polylog(3,x) / (1 - x). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jul 14 2020

A066990.name: In canonical prime factorization of n replace even exponents with 2 and odd exponents with 1.
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = p^(2 - e mod 2), p prime, e>0.

A066991.name: Square array read by antidiagonals of number of ways of dividing nk labeled items into k unlabeled orders with n items in each order.

A066994.name: Numbers n such that phi(n) divides n*sigma(n).

A066995.name: Numbers k such that sigma(k) divides k*phi(k).

A066996.name: Numbers n such that Sum_{i=2..n} 1/A001221(i) is an integer.

A066997.name: Survivor number for 2nd-order Josephus problem.
formula: a(n) = 1+k+2^(m-1) for k < 2^(m-1) and 2^m otherwise, where m = floor(log_2(n)) and k = n-2^m. Also: write n in binary; drop first bit; "OR" new first bit with each remaining bit; append 1 as new first bit; convert to integer; add 1.

A066998.name: a(0)=0; a(n) = n^2*a(n-1) + 1.
formula: Sum_{n>=0} a(n) * x^n / (n!)^2 = (BesselI(0,2*sqrt(x)) - 1) / (1 - x). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jan 23 2021
